    {
        "content": "<p>How should the covering relation be called in lemmas? So far, I've been using <code>a_covers_b</code> to mean <code>a ⋖ b</code>, aka \"<code>b</code> covers <code>a</code>\". Is the obvious swap fine by you? Do you have any better suggestion?</p>",
        "id": 269390899,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1643194174
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Could you swap the symbol?</p>",
        "id": 269390984,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1643194207
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If you write <code>b .&gt; a</code> instead...</p>",
        "id": 269391034,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1643194240
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Then you can also just name it <code>b_covers_a</code>. And there will be much rejoicing <span aria-label=\"stuck out tongue wink\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f61c\" role=\"img\" title=\"stuck out tongue wink\">:stuck_out_tongue_wink:</span></p>",
        "id": 269391071,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1643194265
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But <code>a ⋖ b → a &lt; b</code> <span aria-label=\"sad\" class=\"emoji emoji-2639\" role=\"img\" title=\"sad\">:sad:</span></p>",
        "id": 269391511,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1643194499
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The best I can come with is <code>a_covby_b</code></p>",
        "id": 269391787,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1643194653
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That's mystifying</p>",
        "id": 269391817,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1643194677
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Either way, that's pretty orthogonal to this PR, right?</p>",
        "id": 269391882,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1643194696
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"387244\">Yaël Dillies</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/144837-PR-reviews/topic/.2311602.20Semimodular.20lattices/near/269391511\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>But <code>a ⋖ b → a &lt; b</code> <span aria-label=\"sad\" class=\"emoji emoji-2639\" role=\"img\" title=\"sad\">:sad:</span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Definitionally, it shouldn't matter if you swap one of the symbols, right?</p>",
        "id": 269391893,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1643194702
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Sure, but the smaller stuff always has been on the LHS.</p>",
        "id": 269391939,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1643194726
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>What's the notation defined as? <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/find/covers\">docs#covers</a>?</p>",
        "id": 269434066,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1643212607
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>a_covers_b</code> is the right name for lemmas about <code>covers a b</code>. It sounds like the problem is that <code>covers a b</code> itself is misnamed</p>",
        "id": 269437291,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1643213667
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes, agreed.</p>",
        "id": 269437372,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
